{"title_page": "Tomochika Tsuboi", "text_new": "{{short description|Japanese baseball player}}\n{{Infobox baseball biography\n| name          = Tomochika Tsuboi\n| image         = OB-Tomochika-Tsuboi20110615.jpg\n| image_size    = 250px\n| team          = Yokohama DeNA BayStars  \n| number        = 77\n| position      = Outfielder / Coach\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1974|02|19}}\n| birth_place    = Tokyo\n| bats          = Left\n| throws        = Left\n| debutleague   = [[Nippon Professional Baseball|NPB]]\n| debutdate     = April 3\n| debutyear     = 1998\n| debutteam     = Hanshin Tigers\n| statyear      = \n| statleague    = NPB\n| stat1label    = At bats\n| stat1value    = 3348\n| stat2label    = Hits\n| stat2value    = 976\n| stat3label    = RBIs\n| stat3value    = 265\n| teams         = \n'''As player'''\n*[[Hanshin Tigers]] ({{npby|1998}}\u2013{{npby|2002}})\n*[[Hokkaido Nippon-Ham Fighters|Nippon-Ham Fighters<br />Hokkaido Nippon-Ham Fighters]] ({{npby|2003}}\u2013{{npby|2010}})\n*[[Orix Buffaloes]] ({{npby|2011}})\n*[[San Rafael Pacifics]] ({{baseball year|2012}})\n*[[Gary SouthShore RailCats]] ({{baseball year|2012}})\n*[[Rio Grande Valley WhiteWings]] ({{baseball year|2012}})\n*[[Edinburg Roadrunners]] ({{baseball year|2013}})\n*[[Lancaster Barnstormers]] ({{baseball year|2014}})\n'''As coach'''\n*[[Yokohama DeNA BayStars]] ({{npby|2015}} \u2013 present)\n| highlights    = \n| update        = 28 August 2013\n}}\n\n'''Tomochika Tsuboi''' ({{lang-ja|'''\u576a\u4e95 \u667a\u54c9'''}}, born February 19, 1974 in [[K\u014dt\u014d, Tokyo]], Japan) is a Japanese [[baseball]] [[outfielder]]. He previously played in the [[Nippon Professional Baseball|NPB]] for 13 seasons, starting in 1998. His professional career started with the [[Hanshin Tigers]], but he was traded to the [[Hokkaido Nippon-Ham Fighters|Nippon-Ham Fighters]] for [[Toshihiro Noguchi]] after the 2002 season. His stint with Nippon Ham was his longest with the same team, lasting through 2010. He then played briefly for the [[Orix Buffaloes]], his final season in Japanese pro ball. He declined a coaching position with the Fighters and since 2012 has played in various American [[independent league baseball|independent leagues]].\n\n==Biography==\n\n{{Empty section|date=July 2010}}\n\n==NPB statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\"\n! SEASON !! TEAM !! G   !! AB  !!  R  !!  H  !! 2B !! 3B !! HR !! RBI !! BB !! SO !! SB !! CS !! AVG  \n|-\n| 1998 || [[Hanshin Tigers|HT]] || 123 || 413 || 63 || 135 || 26 || 2 || 2 || 21 || 38 || 80 || 7 || 5 || .327 \n|-\n| 1999 || [[Hanshin Tigers|HT]] ||134||530||75||161||30||1||5|| 43 || 50 || 90 || 6 || 10 || .304 \n|-\n| 2000 || [[Hanshin Tigers|HT]]  ||128||489||49||133||14||4||4||32 || 50 || 83 || 6 || 6 || .272 \n|-\n| 2001 || [[Hanshin Tigers|HT]] ||43||128||12||28||7||2||2||11 || 11 || 30 || 1|| 1 || .219 \n|-\n| 2002 || [[Hanshin Tigers|HT]] ||24||68||8||17||3||0||1||6 || 5 || 19 || 1 || 0 || .250 \n|-\n| 2003 || [[Hokkaido Nippon-Ham Fighters|NHF]]  ||123||443||70||146||26||3||5||40 || 52 || 79 || 13 || 5 || .330 \n|-\n| 2004 || [[Hokkaido Nippon-Ham Fighters|HNHF]] ||89||359||53||102||23||2||11||43 || 43 || 64 || 4 || 6 || .284 \n|-\n| 2005 || [[Hokkaido Nippon-Ham Fighters|HNHF]] ||98||314||39||97||10||1||2||19 || 31 || 54 || 5 || 3 || .309 \n|-\n| 2006 || [[Hokkaido Nippon-Ham Fighters|HNHF]] ||25||47||4||9||2||0||0||1 || 2 || 10 || 0 || 0 || .191  \n|-\n| 2007 || [[Hokkaido Nippon-Ham Fighters|HNHF]] ||100||276||26||78||7||2||0 || 23 || 17 || 53 || 6 || 2 || .283\n|-\n| 2008 || [[Hokkaido Nippon-Ham Fighters|HNHF]] ||26||50||2||11||2||0||0||1 || 1 || 7 || 0 || 0 || .220\n|-\n| 2009 || [[Hokkaido Nippon-Ham Fighters|HNHF]] ||84||146||13||39||8||0||0||15 || 5 || 23 || 0 || 0 || .267\n|-\n| 2010 || [[Hokkaido Nippon-Ham Fighters|HNHF]] ||36||77||7||18||3||1||0||9 || 4 || 19 || 1 || 0 || .234\n|-\n| 2011 || [[Orix Buffaloes|OBs]] ||3||8||0||2||1||0||0||1 || 0 || 2 || 0 || 0 || .250\n|-\n| T